obo:HP_0009614 obo:IAO_0000115 This term applies if the proximal phalanx of the thumb is partially duplicated. Depending on the severity, the appearance on x-ray can vary from a notched phalanx the duplicated bone is almost completely fused with the phalanx to a partially fused appearance of the two bones.
